# No Deletion Without Explicit Permission

**NEVER** delete, remove, or `git rm` any file or directory on this computer without the user explicitly saying "yes, delete it" or "you have permission to delete".

## Applies To
- `delete_file` tool calls
- Shell commands: `rm`, `git rm`, `rmdir`, `trash`, etc.
- Any operation that destroys or removes files from disk or git history

## Required Before Any Deletion
- State exactly what will be deleted and why
- Wait for explicit user approval before proceeding

## Example
- ❌ Deciding to `git rm -r docs/` as part of a refactor without asking
- ✅ "I need to delete `docs/` — do I have your permission to remove it?"
